The paper deals with a search problem on trees, which is a fundamental topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of unreliable guiding instructions and the probabilistic setting suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of the efficiency of the search algorithm involves concepts from information theory, such as entropy, which may place the paper in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents bounds on the complexity of the search algorithm, which is a common topic in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of probabilistic models and the analysis of the noise parameter suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
